# Elevated section cards

Use **full-width elevated** cards for form sections on add, edit, and detail pages (same pattern as `apps/pm/app/projects/add/page.js`).

## Pattern

- Page shell: `space-y-6 p-4 md:p-6` (no `max-w-*` on the form wrapper).
- Each section: `Card` with `variant="elevated"` and `className={ELEVATED_SECTION_CARD_CLASS}` from `@greenways/ui`.
- `ELEVATED_SECTION_CARD_CLASS` is `w-full rounded-xl` (built-in shadow from `Card` elevated variant).
- Section title: `SectionCardTitleContent` with icon + label, or `Card` `title` / `subtitle` props.
- Alternative: `FormSectionCard` (already applies `ELEVATED_SECTION_CARD_CLASS` by default).

## Example

```jsx
import { Card, ELEVATED_SECTION_CARD_CLASS, SectionCardTitleContent, Input } from '@greenways/ui'

<Card
  variant="elevated"
  className={ELEVATED_SECTION_CARD_CLASS}
  title={<SectionCardTitleContent icon={FolderOpen} label="Section title" />}
  subtitle="Short description of this section."
>
  {/* fields */}
</Card>
```

## Do not

- Wrap section forms in `max-w-3xl` unless a deliberate narrow layout is required.
- Place section content directly on the page background without an elevated `Card`.
- Use ad-hoc `border shadow-sm` overrides instead of `variant="elevated"`.
